<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4387685>
        a                        fabio:Figure ;
        dc:description           "FIGURE 4. Sphingius barkudensis Gravely, 1931. A–B left pedipalp (ADSH562702):A ventral; B retrolateral. C–D ♀ genitalia (ADSH562702): C epigynum, ventral; D vulva, dorsal. Abbreviations: AH anterior epigynal hood, B bursa, C conductor, CO copulatory opening, CD copulatory duct, E embolus, EB embolic base, EP epigynal plate, FD fertilization duct, MA median tegular apophysis, PP prolateral process of median tegular apophysis, RTA retrolateral tibial apophysis, S spermatheca, T tegulum. Arrow indicates cymbial dorsal mat of hairs. Scale bars: A–D, 0.2 mm." ;
